snippet.textDisplay: Jhumur -  has its roots amongst the tribals/indigenous peoples of eastern india, primarily the Santals. The cultural dynamics has given many representations of Jhumur and therefore it is found in folk cultures of Bengali, Assamese and others, with their own lyrics. It's a dance form performed with singing song in a rhythmic setting, preserving the original Santali Jhumur tune.
snippet.textOriginal: Jhumur -  has its roots amongst the tribals/indigenous peoples of eastern india, primarily the Santals. The cultural dynamics has given many representations of Jhumur and therefore it is found in folk cultures of Bengali, Assamese and others, with their own lyrics. It's a dance form performed with singing song in a rhythmic setting, preserving the original Santali Jhumur tune.
